{{Infobox person | name = Ayman Sabawi Ibrahim | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1971|10|21}} | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = [[Iraqi people|Iraqi]] | other_names = | known_for = Member of the Iraqi insurgency | occupation = }}
'''Ayman Sabawi Ibrahim Hasan''' ({{lang-ar|<big>أيمن سبعاوي إبراهيم</big>}}) (born 21 October 1971)<ref>[https://archive.is/20121218201616/http://www.gov.im/infocentre/ViewNews.gov?page=lib/news/treasury/customs/unitednationssan3.xml&menuid=10160 United Nations Sanctions - Iraq - Customs Sanctions Notices] myGov.im</ref> is [[Saddam Hussein]]'s half-nephew and a suspected [[guerrilla]]. Ayman's father is [[Sabawi Ibrahim Hassan al-Tikriti]], Saddam's half brother who was captured in [[Tikrit]] in February, 2005. Ayman was suspected of aiding the [[Iraqi insurgency (2003–11)|Iraqi Insurgency]] and was arrested at the beginning of May, 2005 during a raid north of Tikrit.
Ayman Ibrahim, who was serving a life sentence in a northern Iraqi prison, escaped with the help of a police officer on December 9, 2006. [https://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/20061209/ap_on_re_mi_ea/iraq_saddam_s_nephew]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}
In 2014 he was involved in the [[Camp Speicher massacre]].
