'''Raquel Naa Ayorkor Ammah''' (born 12 August 1987) and known by stage name '''Raquel,''' is a [[Ghana|Ghanaian]] musician, composer, choreographer, actress and script writer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=One-on-one interview with Raquel|url=https://www.modernghana.com/music/25863/one-on-one-interview-with-raquel.html|website=modernghana.com|publisher=afromusion|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|title=Raquel Profile|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref> She is popularly known for her hit song “Sweetio” which featured [[Sarkodie (rapper)|Sarkodie]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile:|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=one-on-one interview with Raquel|url=https://www.modernghana.com/music/25863/one-on-one-interview-with-raquel.html|website=modernghana.com|publisher=afrofusion|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Adinkra|first1=Fiifi|title=Raquel – Sweetio (Feat Sarkodie)|url=http://www.ghanandwom.net/raquel-sweetio-feat-sarkodie/|website=ghanandwom.net|publisher=ghanandwom.net|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref>
==Early life== Raquel was born in the [[United Kingdom]] by [[Ghanaian]] parents.<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref> She grew up in [[West London (sub region)|West London]] with her mother and three other siblings- Two brothers and a sister.<ref>{{cite web|title=One-on-one interview with Raquel|url=https://www.modernghana.com/music/25863/one-on-one-interview-with-raquel.html|website=modernghana.com|publisher=Afromusion|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref> Raquel attended many schools because her family moved houses a few times. However, her favourite schools remained Hogarth Primary School based in Chiswick, and West Thames College.<ref>{{cite web|title=One-on-one interview with Raquel|url=https://www.modernghana.com/music/25863/one-on-one-interview-with-raquel.html|website=modernghana.com|publisher=Afromusion|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref>
==Career== Raquel officially entered the music scene in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|title=One-on-one interview with Raquel|url=https://www.modernghana.com/music/25863/one-on-one-interview-with-raquel.html|website=modernghana.com|publisher=Afromusion|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref> and has since shared same stage with international acts like [[Mario]], [[Movado]],Young (U.S) Lloyd (U.S), Kas (Nigeria), [[Cabbo Snoop]] (Angola), [[Duncan Mighty]] (Nigeria), [[Stephanie Benson]] (UK/Ghana).<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref> She released ‘Odo’ as her official hit [[single (music)|single]] in July 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref>
==Philanthropy== As part of her social responsibility, Raquel has voluntarily been a mentor for a private charity within her local community in Ghana called Christ Humanitarian Foundation (CHF).<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref> She acts as a public advocate for the foundation to help them raise funds each year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref>
==Awards and nominations== She won the Best Female Artist 2012, at the YFM All Star Weekend Awards, December, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref> She also had one nomination at the Hip Hop and RnB Awards 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Raquel Profile|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=1274|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb.com|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref>
